thm T6_PERFECT_NUMBERS_DECISION [tags: perfect-numbers, open-problem, MSC-11A25]
  stmt: The set of perfect numbers is finite or infinite.
  proof_attempt:
    Direct infinitude route: Euclid gives a perfect number from each Mersenne prime exponent [C-001], but no proof supplies infinitely many such exponents.
    [GAP: infinitude of Mersenne primes | suffices: prove infinitely many primes p with 2^p-1 prime]
    Direct finiteness route: Euler classifies even perfect numbers [C-002], but finiteness would require finitely many Mersenne primes and exclusion or finite bounding of odd perfect numbers.
    [GAP: finite bound for odd perfect numbers and Mersenne prime exponents | suffices: prove no odd perfect numbers and finitely many Mersenne primes, or another exhaustive bound]
  status: not proved.
